import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
sns.set(style="whitegrid")

student=pd.read_csv('StudentsPerformance.csv')
student.head()
#performance  varies with respect to parental level of education,race/ethnicity,gender.(considered only math score)
ax = sns.barplot(x=student['math score'], y='race/ethnicity', data=student)
ax=sns.barplot(x='math score', y='parental level of education',data=student)
ax=sns.barplot(x='math score', y='gender',data=student)

ax = sns.barplot(x=student['lunch'], y='writing score', data=student)
#we can conclude that exam performance of students having standard lunch are more better.
#3:whether the preparation courses have an impact on exam performance
ax = sns.barplot(x=student['test preparation course'], y='math score', data=student)
ax = sns.barplot(x=student['test preparation course'], y='reading score', data=student)
